		<seealso cref="System.Windows.Forms.ComboBox"/>
		<seealso cref="System.Windows.Forms.CheckedListBox"/>
		<seealso cref="System.Windows.Forms.MenuItem"/>
		<seealso cref="System.Windows.Forms.MeasureItemEventHandler"/>
	</doc>
	<doc for="MeasureItemEventArgs.Graphics">
		<summary>
			<para>Gets the <see cref="System.Drawing.Graphics"/> object to
   measure against.</para>
		</summary>
		<value>
			<para>The <see cref="System.Drawing.Graphics"/> object to use to determine the scale of the item
   you are drawing.</para>
		</value>
		<remarks>
			<para>You use a <see cref="System.Drawing.Graphics"/> object to determine the scale to use when
   setting the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.MeasureItemEventArgs.ItemHeight"/> and <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.MeasureItemEventArgs.ItemWidth"/>. Different types of graphics objects can
   have different scales, such as the difference in measurement scale between a
   monitor screen and a printer.</para>
		</remarks>
		<example>
			<codelink SampleID="MeasureItemEventArgs" SnippetID="1"/>
		</example>
	</doc>
